File: A pair of handcuffs seen on a desk. JOHANNESBURG - A multiple murder accused eThekwini ANC councillor and another party member has been granted bail of R5,000 each. The pair is alleged to have masterminded the Inanda drive-by shooting in which three people were killed and five wounded last year just before municipal elections. Themba Mnguni and Nomthandazo Mbeje appeared in the Ntuzuma Magistrates Court. READ:Â Crime in SA | 3 ANC members shot dead in Inanda Meanwhile, community members in the area are upset that the suspects were granted bail. They are appealing to the ANC to remove the accused from their positions. They gathered outside the court to protest.